Stats also works fine with pure []float64 data. The types allow for a very clean API for working with data and statistics. You can compare using functions[1] or methods[2] in /examples.<p>I started with only []float64 but wanted to allow stuff like this:<p><pre><code>    func getData() []float64 {
    	// Do stuff to get the data and 
    	// store it in var data []float64
    	return data
    }

    var d Float64Data = getData()
    fmt.Println(d.Max())
</code></pre>
